"And breeds such as poodles have to be highly trimmed."
; McFadden said he handles an average of 20 to 25 dogs at each show and works around 120 shows a year all over the U.S.
The dogs are frequent winners in best of breed and best of show categories.
"We finish with close to 100 champions a year," he said.; As a handler, McFadden emphasizes that he doesn't do obedience training.
The aim, he said, is to have a "confident and happy dog" entering a competition.; Over the last seven years, McFadden and his wife have shown dogs representing approximately 75 percent of the 135 breeds of dog.
